[String], compressionLevel: Int, jarFactory: JarFactory, plugins: List[Plugin]) extends FileWriter {\\n    //keep these imports local - avoid confusion with scala naming\\n    import java.util.jar.Attributes.Name.{MANIFEST_VERSION, MAIN_CLASS}\\n    import java.util.jar.{JarOutputStream, Manifest}\\n\\n    val storeOnly = compressionLevel == Deflater.NO_COMPRESSION\\n\\n\\n[136 more lines in file. Use offset=195 to continue.]\"}], \"isError\": false, \"timestamp\": 1778005481029}]}\n/home/mihailo/git/reachability-copy/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/logs/org.scala-lang:scala-compiler:2.13.8/add-new-library-support/pi-generation-2026-05-05T18-32-35-352943Z.log:3140:[recv] {\"type\": \"message_end\", \"message\": {\"role\": \"assistant\", \"content\": [{\"type\": \"thinking\", \"thinking\": \"**Considering compilation options**\\n\\nI'm looking into compiling with the -d jar option, which might trigger the YjarFactory default through reflection. That sounds promising! The DocFactory's HtmlFactory resources include scaldoc documents, which activate the HtmlFactory's anonymous resources. I might also need to consider the DocFactory itself. I think I’ll need a temporary source and output, so I should check if I can use scala.tools.nsc.doc.Settings. Inspecting that constructor could help clarify things!\", \"thinkingSignature\": \"{\\\"id\\\":\\\"rs_04ef86d37b8abc700169fa35eb9ee481a1bd09a4d6d4cd5f28\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"encrypted_content\\\":\\\"gAAAAABp-jXteWRNS93x2oS9t9OI-4TNDmB7XwbRgTtjAZgOA0DHxq7AFechYvWlENhqYUCQ2f3pw593Vsm3UPXfvXZULBuSYVsvWdTXiyMvGHKftVpQC0ZbkUI1VY7-Tl3RKzKQ80lWIyrf2H70Dk29YVp4RPQTlK0wuVlw1o-YbyLUKEKI15UaPqANMYxV0iC-y7gwLxSe6-pZYswoQYtJ_5E39EDZ3_rh2vCNIHT00SSykEmSAeSqueeU2b0VN9uNUF9HRDsDMNFCadToPUE9M1Vt4GwnTnYZoTxPiQad35h9Rtsff5wKENwCQJSyED-zWIyosKXTefvFKh_303Syh1ANz94-Uo7UwVr8cYj-uolL-cC9K7Vf_YV6keLiGrdigEb4xcI1hG-b7Sr7wGs1jY6Xnk32u1DeD1DKDgl_pSc-BkNObu7WL9zc92s59C_ibjzyx16881Bb1ib_9GXWeOvpZ-OTdcu5jRgoqR0sZQnAzkVPOq8prLwRb1w3Ri